ores at its height as freezers became more popular frozen food departments were designed into sainsburys main supermarkets and the chain was sold to bejam in  who were ultimately sold to iceland in  sainsburys savacentre main article savacentre savacentre was a chain of  hypermarkets and  discount supermarkets operated between  and  initially in a joint venture with bhs the stores ranged in size between  sq ft  m and  sq ft  m and the discount supermarkets between  sq ft  m and  sq ft  m at the time of its inception it was the only dedicated hypermarket chain in the uk store layout consisted of a  split between food and nonfood shopping with a complete range of both retailers products and later included input from habitat and mothercare as they merged with bhs some stores also included features such as a petrol station and instore cafe in  sainsburys bought out bhss half stake but still allowed bhs to retail from savacentres until they offered its own clothing and merchandise offering sainsburys calais wine store sainsburys operated one alcohol hypermarket in partnership with auchan in calais france for the lucrative uk booze cruise market the store closed in  after describing the operation as economically unviable sainsburys market in  sainsburys opened an experimental store in the bluebird building in chelsea london the concept of the market store was to provide a large range of fresh meat fish delicatessen items and bread through colleagues serving over counters colleagues were specially hired for their skill and passion for their roles in store the layout also provided a larger than usual area for retailing fresh produce the store closed in  after poor results a second much larger version in pimlico was designated as a market store but the stores branding and layout was gradually reverted to a standard sainsburys store fresh kitchen in  sainsburys opened a trial food to go shop in fleet street london selling sandwiches baguettes and hot snacks in an effort to expand its business into new areas of opportunity the store closed a year later after the stores lease was not renewed sainsburys commented that footfall was too high to offer high standards of quality and service however it was not ruling out performing another trial in another location explaining that it had learnt a lot mobile by sainsburys main article mobile by sainsburys sainsburys operated a virtual mobile network from  until  which closed due to being commercially unsustainable in  sainsburys reentered the uk telecommunications industry when it launched a mobile phone network called mobile by sainsburys the virtual network was operated in partnership with vodafone the network was promoted heavily in store and most supermarkets started retailing sim cards and handsets for the network however in  sainsburys announced that the service would be closing in january  after a breakdown in the relationship with its provider vodafone sainsburys compare and save sainsburys compare and save was a comparison and switching service website that promoted a wide range of television broadband and telephone deals from a variety of providers the service free to sainsburys customers claimed to list  different packages the website and service launched in  and was operated by simplifydigital sainsburys pharmacy sainsburys operated  pharmacies within its supermarkets  sainsburys was also a provider of outpatient hospital pharmacy services operating pharmacies at three major uk hospitals guys hospital st thomas hospital and james cook university hospital in july  sainsburys announced they were selling their  pharmacies to lloydspharmacy for £ million in  with all  pharmacy employees being transferred over and new rent agreements being made sainsburys entertainment sainsburys entertainment was a transactional website which provided films as downloads or for streaming using rovi corporation software the site arranged to register with atvod as a video on demand service the website also sold mp downloads as well as ebooks through anobii the site began operating in  and until march  also sold physical products including dvds cds bluray discs and books these were posted to the customer by a distributor which after  was sainsburys subsidiary company global media vault ltd customers received nectar points from shopping at sainsburys entertainment sainsburys announced in september  that it would close the business on  november  product rangesedit a large store typically stocks around  lines of which around  are ownlabel goods these ownbrand lines include the own label basics range is its low cost products name description basics an economy range of around  lines mainly food but also including other areas such as toiletries and stationery the basics range uses minimal packaging with simple orange and white designs sainsburys local stores sell none or very few of these lines equivalent to tescos everyday value asdas smart price and morrisons m savers additional product lines were added in late  together with new packaging by sainsburys all ownbrand food products that are not part of any of the other ranges over  different lines have been rebranded as by sainsburys this was first introduced on frozen foods in late  and the rebranding was completed in january  taste the difference premiumquality brand containing around  food lines including many processed foods such as readymade meals and premium bakery lines the range consisting of  lines was relaunched in september  when  of the range was improved or newly added similar to asdas extra special tescos finest and morrisons the best be good to yourself products with reduced calorific andor fat content the bgty range was relaunched in january  delicously freefrom launched in  it has over  product lines these products are all grouped together in one aisle of the store except fresh and frozen lines these products are suitable for those allergic to dairy wheat and gluten although some are free from wheatgluten but