udoe said “our goal is to make our customers lives easier and deliver the best shopping experience  whether in store at home or on the go there’s a huge opportunity in this fastchanging part of our business and i’m excited to take on the challenge“sainsbury’s first launched its online grocery business in  and now regularly serves  customers a week delivering to  per cent of uk postcodes it is growing strongly at  per cent per year driven by a combined focus on technology and marketing as well as customer service and product availability”rudoe joins the group development division reporting to luke jenson group development directorjenson said “maximising new and existing opportunities in the online and digital space is a key part of our longterm strategy for growth we’re focused on finding new ways to deliver a compelling digital experience to customers across a range of products and services from ebooks to mobile scan  go”rudoe joined sainsbury’s in july  from ocado where he was head of retailthis article is about uk sainsburys digital mobileshare to twittershare to linkedinshare to facebookget the newsletterkeep up to date with the latest news and insightssubscribeishbel macleodim social media manager from the drumi also cover social media newsall by ishbel lets get social join us on linkedinfollow us on twitterfind us on facebookfind us on instagram related articlesuksainsburysdigitalmobiledrum newsmobile campaign aims to end child solitary confinement by transporting viewers inside a cramped july chariot the commuter shuttle from ford is en route to new york july opinionhow brands can capitalise on the addressable tv revolution may laura jordan bambach and logan wilmont review the latest creative from sainsbury’s gosh and february more must watchvideoinside the san miguel experience why the brand is investing in immersive eventsvideotina brown author of the diana chronicles on what makes a great storyvideosmiley’s ceo wants to turn the emoji’s godfather from a lic